8.12	WaYao	Yao people (East Africa)	The Yao people, Wayao, are a major ethnic and linguistic group based at the southern end of Lake Malawi, which played an important part in the history of East Africa during the 19th century. The Yao are a predominantly Muslim people group of about 2 million spread over three countries, Malawi, Mozambique and Tanzania. The Yao people have a strong cultural identity, which transcend the national borders.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/31/Initiation_ritual_of_boys_in_Malawi.jpg/300px-Initiation_ritual_of_boys_in_Malawi.jpg
